oup.com/setup-net-development-environment-ubuntu/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Getting Started with C++ and Visual Studio Code on Ubuntu</title> <author>vkantchev</author> <category>cpp</category> <category>linux</category> <category>ubuntu</category> <category>vscode</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Getting Started with C++ and Visual Studio Code on Ubuntu&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Before going through these steps make sure you have done &lt;a href=&#34;/setup-cpp-development-environment-ubuntu&#34;&gt;Setup C++ development environment on Ubuntu&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/getting-started-cpp-visual-studio-code-ubuntu/</link> <pubDate>Sat, 18 Nov 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/feed_rss_created.xml">Swift Software Group Blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/getting-started-cpp-visual-studio-code-ubuntu/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Setup C++ development environment on Ubuntu</title> <author>vkantchev</author> <category>cpp</category> <category>linux</category> <category>ubuntu</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Setup C++ development environment on Ubuntu&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;These steps were tested on Ubuntu 22.04.3 LTS. Scripts are &lt;code&gt;bash&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Compilers&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;bashsudo apt install build-essential&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/setup-cpp-development-environment-ubuntu/</link> <pubDate>Fri, 17 Nov 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/feed_rss_created.xml">Swift Software Group Blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/setup-cpp-development-environment-ubuntu/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Getting Started with .NET and Visual Studio Code on macOS</title> <author>vkantchev</author> <category>csharp</category> <category>dotnet</category> <category>macos</category> <category>vscode</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Getting Started with .NET and Visual Studio Code on macOS&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Before going through these steps make sure you have done &lt;a href=&#34;/setup-net-development-environment-macos&#34;&gt;Setup .NET development environment on macOS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Visual Studio Code&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Download and install from &lt;a href=&#34;https://code.visualstudio.com/download&#34;&gt;Visual Studio Code&lt;/a&gt; site. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Open Visual Studio Code and press &lt;code&gt;Cmd + Shift + p&lt;/code&gt;. Select &lt;code&gt;Shell Command: Install &#39;code&#39; command in PATH&lt;/code&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Close Visual Studio Code.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/getting-started-net-visual-studio-code-macos/</link> <pubDate>Wed, 15 Nov 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/feed_rss_created.xml">Swift Software Group Blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/getting-started-net-visual-studio-code-macos/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Setup .NET development environment on macOS</title> <author>vkantchev</author> <category>csharp</category> <category>dotnet</category> <category>macos</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Setup .NET development environment on macOS&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h1&gt;Setup for macOS&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Download the &lt;code&gt;dotnet-install.sh&lt;/code&gt; script&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;bashcdcurl -sSL https://dot.net/v1/dotnet-install.sh &amp;gt; dotnet-install.shchmod +x dotnet-install.sh&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/setup-net-development-environment-macos/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 14 Nov 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/feed_rss_created.xml">Swift Software Group Blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/setup-net-development-environment-macos/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Configure Ruby Environment on Ubuntu</title> <author>vkantchev</author> <category>linux</category> <category>ruby</category> <category>ubuntu</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Configure Ruby Environment on Ubuntu&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is a simple guide for configuring a Ruby 2 environment on Ubuntu. This was tested for Ruby 2.7.2 on Ubuntu 22.04.3. All scripts are &lt;code&gt;bash&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/configure-ruby-environment-ubuntu/</link> <pubDate>Sun, 08 Oct 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/feed_rss_created.xml">Swift Software Group Blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/configure-ruby-environment-ubuntu/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Getting Started with C++ and Visual Studio Code on macOS</title> <author>vkantchev</author> <category>cpp</category> <category>macos</category> <category>vscode</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Getting Started with C++ and Visual Studio Code on macOS&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Before going through these steps make sure you have done &lt;a href=&#34;/setup-cpp-development-environment-macos&#34;&gt;Setup C++ development environment on macOS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Visual Studio Code&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Download and install from &lt;a href=&#34;https://code.visualstudio.com/download&#34;&gt;Visual Studio Code&lt;/a&gt; site.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Open Visual Studio Code and press &lt;code&gt;Cmd + Shift + p&lt;/code&gt;. Select &lt;code&gt;Shell Command: Install &#39;code&#39; command in PATH&lt;/code&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/getting-started-cpp-visual-studio-code-macos/</link> <pubDate>Sat, 07 Oct 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/feed_rss_created.xml">Swift Software Group Blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/getting-started-cpp-visual-studio-code-macos/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Setup C++ development environment on macOS</title> <author>vkantchev</author> <category>cpp</category> <category>macos</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Setup C++ development environment on macOS&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Homebrew&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Install Homebrew:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;bash/bin/bash -c &#34;$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)&#34;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/setup-cpp-development-environment-macos/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 12 Sep 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/feed_rss_created.xml">Swift Software Group Blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/setup-cpp-development-environment-macos/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Configure Ruby Environment on Windows</title> <author>vkantchev</author> <category>ruby</category> <category>windows</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Configure Ruby Environment on Windows&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is a simple guide for configuring a Ruby 2 environment on Windows 11. All scripts are PowerShell.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;PowerShell&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;This will allow you to execute PowerShell scripts locally on your machine. In PowerShell as Administrator:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;powershellSet-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope LocalMachine&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/configure-ruby-environment-windows/</link> <pubDate>Sat, 27 May 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/feed_rss_created.xml">Swift Software Group Blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/configure-ruby-environment-windows/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Run MongoDB with Podman</title> <author>vkantchev</author> <category>mongodb</category> <category>podman</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Run MongoDB with Podman&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Before you start install &lt;a href=&#34;/setup-podman-macos&#34;&gt;Podman&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Set machine to &lt;code&gt;rootful&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;bashpodman machine stoppodman machine set --rootfulpodman machine start&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/run-mongodb-with-podman/</link> <pubDate>Tue, 23 May 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/feed_rss_created.xml">Swift Software Group Blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/run-mongodb-with-podman/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Setup Podman on macOS</title> <author>vkantchev</author> <category>macos</category> <category>podman</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Setup Podman on macOS&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Podman is a utility that can be used to create and maintain containers. This post will teach you how to set up Podman on macOS and perform some basic commands.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/setup-podman-macos/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 22 May 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/feed_rss_created.xml">Swift Software Group Blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/setup-podman-macos/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Deploy Docker Swarm on AWS EC2 via cloud-formation templates - Step 1 - Network Setup</title> <author>vkantchev</author> <category>aws</category> <category>cloud</category> <category>cloud-formation</category> <category>docker</category> <category>docker-swarm</category> <category>ec2</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Deploy Docker Swarm on AWS EC2 via cloud-formation templates - Step 1 - Network Setup&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Setup network infrastructure including new VPC (Virtual Private Cloud), public and private subnets, internet gateway, security group, and ssh access.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This post is part of a thread that includes these steps:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Network Setup (this post)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/deploy-docker-swarm-aws-ec2-cloudformation-step-2-storage&#34;&gt;Storage&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/deploy-docker-swarm-aws-ec2-cloudformation-step-3-roles&#34;&gt;Roles&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/deploy-docker-swarm-aws-ec2-cloudformation-step-4-manager-instance&#34;&gt;Manager Instance&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/deploy-docker-swarm-aws-ec2-cloudformation-step-5-worker-launch-template&#34;&gt;Worker Launch Template&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/deploy-docker-swarm-aws-ec2-cloudformation-step-6-worker-instances&#34;&gt;Worker Instances&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/deploy-docker-swarm-aws-ec2-cloudformation-step-7-docker-swarm&#34;&gt;Docker Swarm&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;/deploy-docker-swarm-aws-ec2-cloudformation-step-8-cleanup&#34;&gt;Cleanup&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;</description><link>https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/deploy-docker-swarm-aws-ec2-cloudformation-step-1-network-setup/</link> <pubDate>Wed, 11 Aug 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/feed_rss_created.xml">Swift Software Group Blog</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://blog.swiftsoftwaregroup.com/deploy-docker-swarm-aws-ec2-cloudformation-step-1-network-setup/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Deploy Docker Swarm on AWS EC2 via cloud-formation templates - Step 2 - Storage</title> <author>vkantchev</author> <category>aws</category> <category>cloud</category> <category>cloud-formation</category> <category>docker</category> <category>docker-swarm</category> <category>ec2</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Deploy Docker Swarm on AWS EC2 via cloud-formation templates - Step 2 - Storage&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this step we will create a shared EBS volume which will be used as a home directory for the Linux users.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This post is part of a thread that includes these steps:&lt;/p&g